verses.text: And Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem , and called for the elders of Israel , and for their heads , and for their judges , and for their officers ; and they presented themselves before God.

And Joshua said unto all the people , Thus saith the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of Israel , Your fathers dwelt on the other side of the flood in old time , \add even\add* Terah , the father of Abraham , and the father of Nachor : and they served other gods.
And I took your father Abraham from the other side of the flood , and led him throughout all the land of Canaan , and multiplied his seed , and gave him Isaac.
And I gave unto Isaac Jacob and Esau : and I gave unto Esau mount Seir , to possess it; but Jacob and his children went down into Egypt.
I sent Moses also and Aaron , and I plagued Egypt , according to that which I did among them: and afterward I brought you out.
And I brought your fathers out of Egypt : and ye came unto the sea ; and the Egyptians pursued after your fathers with chariots and horsemen unto the Red sea.

And when they cried unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, he put darkness between you and the Egyptians , and brought the sea upon them, and covered them; and your eyes have seen what I have done in Egypt : and ye dwelt in the wilderness a long season.

And I brought you into the land of the Amorites , which dwelt on the other side Jordan ; and they fought with you: and I gave them into your hand , that ye might possess their land ; and I destroyed them from before you.
Then Balak the son of Zippor , king of Moab , arose and warred against Israel , and sent and called Balaam the son of Beor to curse you:
But I would not hearken unto Balaam ; therefore he blessed you still : so I delivered you out of his hand.

And ye went over Jordan , and came unto Jericho : and the men of Jericho fought against you, the Amorites , and the Perizzites , and the Canaanites , and the Hittites , and the Girgashites , the Hivites , and the Jebusites ; and I delivered them into your hand.
And I sent the hornet before you, which drave them out from before you, \add even\add* the two kings of the Amorites ; \add but\add* not with thy sword , nor with thy bow.
And I have given you a land for which ye did not labour , and cities which ye built not, and ye dwell in them; of the vineyards and oliveyards which ye planted not do ye eat. \p

¶ Now therefore fear the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, and serve him in sincerity and in truth : and put away the gods which your fathers served on the other side of the flood , and in Egypt ; and serve ye the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*. \p

And if it seem evil unto you to serve the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, choose you this day whom ye will serve ; whether the gods which your fathers served that \add were\add* on the other side of the flood , or the gods of the Amorites , in whose land ye dwell : but as for me and my house , we will serve the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.
And the people answered and said , God forbid that we should forsake the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, to serve other gods ;

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God , he \add it is\add* that brought us up and our fathers out of the land of Egypt , from the house of bondage , and which did those great signs in our sight , and preserved us in all the way wherein we went , and among all the people through whom we passed :

And the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* drave out from before us all the people , even the Amorites which dwelt in the land : \add therefore\add* will we also serve the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; for he \add is\add* our God.

And Joshua said unto the people , Ye cannot serve the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: for he \add is\add* an holy God ; he \add is\add* a jealous God ; he will not forgive your transgressions nor your sins.\f + \fr 24.19 \ft holy God: Heb. holy Gods\f*
If ye forsake the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and serve strange gods , then he will turn and do you hurt , and consume you, after that he hath done you good.
And the people said unto Joshua , Nay; but we will serve the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And Joshua said unto the people , Ye \add are\add* witnesses against yourselves that ye have chosen you the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, to serve him. And they said , \add We are\add* witnesses.
Now therefore put away , \add said he\add*, the strange gods which \add are\add* among you, and incline your heart unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of Israel.
And the people said unto Joshua , The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God will we serve , and his voice will we obey.
So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day , and set them a statute and an ordinance in Shechem. \p

¶ And Joshua wrote these words in the book of the law of God , and took a great stone , and set it up there under an oak , that \add was\add* by the sanctuary of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And Joshua said unto all the people , Behold, this stone shall be a witness unto us; for it hath heard all the words of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* which he spake unto us: it shall be therefore a witness unto you, lest ye deny your God.
So Joshua let the people depart , every man unto his inheritance. \p
¶ And it came to pass after these things , that Joshua the son of Nun , the servant of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, died , \add being\add* an hundred and ten years old.
And they buried him in the border of his inheritance in Timnath-serah , which \add is\add* in mount Ephraim , on the north side of the hill of Gaash.

And Israel served the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* all the days of Joshua , and all the days of the elders that overlived Joshua , and which had known all the works of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, that he had done for Israel.  +  r 24.31  t overlived…: Heb. prolonged their days after Joshua * \p

¶ And the bones of Joseph , which the children of Israel brought up out of Egypt , buried they in Shechem , in a parcel of ground which Jacob bought of the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for an hundred pieces of silver : and it became the inheritance of the children of Joseph.\f + \fr 24.32 \ft pieces…: or, lambs\f*
And Eleazar the son of Aaron died ; and they buried him in a hill \add that pertained to\add* Phinehas his son , which was given him in mount Ephraim.
